  "instructions": [
    "heat vegetable oil in a large pot over medium-high heat. add chopped onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add mustard seeds and caraway seeds and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "add garlic and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "add soaked and drained split peas, beef broth, salt, and black pepper. stir to combine, then bring to a boil.",
    "reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, until peas are tender, about 20 minutes.",
    "stir in whole wheat flour to thicken stew.",
    "add pickled mustard seeds and stir to combine.",
    "serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired.",
    "transfer stew to 6 ramekins, then refrigerate to chill before serving"
